<HEADLINE> NATO Spokesman Says Make-up of Kosovo Force Not Negotiable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The make-up of the future
international security force in Kosovo must be centered around
NATO and is not negotiable, said NATO spokesman James Shea on
Monday.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with radio France-Info in Brussels, Shea said
that it is one thing to have a peace keeping force without rules
of engagement or robust armaments, and another thing to have one
equipped with these.
</P>
<P>
``We know that the situation in Kosovo will be very difficult
once the Serb forces leave. There should be a force which has the
respect of all and which could create a climate of security for
the return of the refugees,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
Shea said that NATO will play an important but not
``monopolist'' role in the future international force in Kosovo,
which could also have troops from Russia and other NATO's partner
countries as its members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
