<HEADLINE> Romania's Main Opposition Appeals for End of NATO </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Party of Social Democracy of
Romania on Monday requested a Parliament's joint session to pass a
statement that should propose an end of air raids on Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The draft statement of the major Opposition mentioned the
losses the Yugoslav and the international communities have
suffered during the two months of war, reading that "from the
beginning of the conflict more than one thousand civilian died and
more than 6,000 injured people were registered and Romania's
losses amount to almost one billion dollars".
</P>
<P>
Specifying that "more than 70 percent of the Romanian public
opinion is in favor of an end of air strikes on Yugoslavia, at
least temporarily", the party proposes that Romania's Parliament
should address an appeal to all the NATO countries, the
Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe and the Parliament
of the Russian Federation to adopt a political stance that should
lead to an end of conflict in Kosovo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
