<HEADLINE> Brazilian FM Visits Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian Foreign Minister Luis
Filipe Lampreia arrived in Luanda on a two-day visit to Angola
showing solidarity with the southern African country.
</P>
<P>
Lampreia told the press at Luanda Airport that "his visit is
aimed at strengthen the existing friendly and cooperative
relationship between Brazil and Angola" to help the two nations
embark on the road to peace, security and the well-being of the
people.
</P>
<P>
The Brazilian minister is scheduled to hold talks with Angolan
leaders on political issues so as to define what kind of help
Brazil can provide to help the war-torn country to achieve peace,
Brazilian Ambassador to Luanda Alexandre Ador Neto said.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that Lampreia has met with his Angolan
counterpart Joao Bernardo Miranda and they have signed an
agreement on mutual exemption of visa for the service passport
holders from the other country. 
</P>
