<HEADLINE> European Social Democrats Call for Fighting Against </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 31 (Xinhua)--Three days before European Union (EU)'s
summit in Cologne, leading Social Democrats from European
countries Monday at their meeting in Bonn urged an effective fight
against the high jobless rate.
</P>
<P>
" It is our first and most important task in Europe," said
German Defence Minister Rudolf Scharping, who hosted the meeting
as chairman of the European Social Democrats.
</P>
<P>
A more concrete employment pact should be passed at the two-day
summit, Scharping said.
</P>
<P>
Amid an overall jobless rate over 8 per cent, the EU has
drafted an employment pact, which is expected to be passed at the
Cologne summit.
</P>
<P>
Former President of European Commission, Jacques Delors,
reminded EU members of their responsibility in the employment
policy.
</P>
<P>
The planned employment pact is not enough for Europa, and EU
should do more to coordinate and control its members' national
policies, said Delors.
</P>
<P>
Another urgent task is to fight against crimes with a common
security policy, said the Social Democrats.
</P>
<P>
Under the common foreign and security policy, the EU members
must find common points in their national interests, and must
concretely decide in which fields to cooperate wisely with each
other, said former Spanish Prime Minister Felips Gonzalez. 
</P>
</TEXT>
