<HEADLINE> Schroeder Recommands Solana EU Coordinator </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, May 31 (Xinhua)--German Chancellor Gerhard Schroeder
Monday indirectly recommended present NATO Secretary General,
Javier Solana, as European Union (EU) coordinator for foreign and
security policies.
</P>
<P>
The former Spanish foreign minister has worked very well in
Brussels, said Schroeder at a presidium session of his Social
Democratic Party (SPD) in Bonn.
</P>
<P>
It won't be bizarre that Schroeder formally nominate Solana for
the post at EU's summit meeting scheduled for June 3 in Cologne,
said SPD's federal manager, Ottmar Scheiner.
</P>
<P>
Solana, whose term in NATO will end in January, 2000, has won
support of Britain, Italy and Spain for the post as "Minister
Europa".
</P>
<P>
But diplomats in Bonn said four neutral EU members remained
reserved towards Solana, saying he stands too close with the
United States. The four countries are Austria, Finland, Sweden
and Ireland.
</P>
<P>
The four countries said Solana's engagement in the Kosovo
crisis would have a negative effect on his support for Europa's
common foreign policy. 
</P>
