<HEADLINE> Envoy Hopes for Positive Outcome of Bonn Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Russian envoy Viktor Chernomyrdin
expressed hope Monday that talks on Yugoslavia on Bonn Tuesday
would yield positive results in bringing a political settlement to
the Balkan crisis.
</P>
<P>
"The week should bring a certain decision...if everything
proceeds according to plan," Chernomyrdin said after a meeting
with Slovak Foreign Minister Eduard Kukan, U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan's envoy for Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Chernomyrdin is scheduled to fly to Bonn Tuesday for a fresh
round of tripartite talks with Finnish President Martti Ahtisaari
and U.S. Deputy Secretary of State Strobe Talbott.
</P>
