<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Aidid's Faction Attacks Against Guerrilla Bases in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, May 31(Xinhua) -- The Somali faction, headed by
Hussein Mohamed Aidid, Sunday afternoon launched reprisal attacks
against the militia positions of the Rahanwein Resistance Army (
RRA) outside Baidoa Town in southern Somalia.
</P>
<P>
Aidid's militia unofficial sources claimed that they have
killed 15 and captured eight RRA fighters , while they have lost
two soldiers and eight others have sustained gunshot wounds.
</P>
<P>
This is the first time that the RRA side does not claim
victory nor talk about inflicting heavy losses on the side of
Aidid.
</P>
<P>
This is the most serious and disastrous fighting for the RRA
since they have intensified their campaign of hit and run against
Aidid in Baidoa town following the rumors that a consignment of
Somali bank notes arrival for Aidid in the town.
</P>
<P>
There's no official word from Aidid's side over the fighting,
but some of his militiamen have declared their determination of
wiping out all of the RRA bases around Baidoa town. Hussein Aidid
is himself in Baidoa town encouraging the clashes.
</P>
<P>
According to reports reaching here from field radios, fierce
fighting broke out around the E1-Don RRA militia base and hundreds
of militiamen of both sides were involved in the fighting.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses in Baidoa said that heavily armed infantry
militiamen from Aidid's side have gone out of the town Sunday
morning to attack the militia RRA bases outside the town.
</P>
<P>
Aidid's militia commanders have apparently changed the tactic
of using battle wagons after the RRA fighters have strengthened
their defensive positions with land mines to seal off all the
roads leading to their bases.
</P>
<P>
The eyewitnesses also said Aidid militiamen surprisingly came
from every corner of E1-Don militia base, which the RRA commanders
were only prepared for battle wagons from their enemies.
</P>
<P>
According to the VHR radio reports, loud noise of the
rocket-propelled grenades,attack hand grenades and machine guns
could be heard throughout Baidoa Sunday afternoon and the early
hours of Monday.
</P>
<P>
The fighting has also been confirmed by the RRA spokesman here
in Mogadishu. The spokesman, Mohamed Ali Aden Qalinleh, said the
fighting has so far reached their militia base at E1-Don, 12Km
North of Baidoa town.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman also confirmed their field radio went out of the
air, an indication that their base was in trouble.
</P>
<P>
Fighting is still continuing, the spokesman said, but he
declined to admit that the base has fallen for Aidid's militiamen.
</P>
<P>
However, independent sources have confirmed that the E1-Don
militia base of the RRA has fallen for Aidid's side Sunday night
and that a counter- attack has Monday been launched by the RRA
fighters in their attempt of regaining control of their base.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
