<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Premier Minister Hun Sen
will pay a working visit to France from June 1 to 3, during which
he will be received by President Jacques Chirac and Prime Minister
Lionel Jospin.
</P>
<P>
A spokesman of the French Foreign Ministry said on Monday that
the visit by Hun Sen will be the first since he was elected
Cambodia's sole prime minister on November 30, 1998, by the
Cambodian parliament.
</P>
<P>
It also comes soon after the entry by Cambodia into the
Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN).
</P>
<P>
Cambodia has received full support from international financial
donors for its economic programs during the Tokyo conference of
the consultative group of the World Bank last February, said the
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
International financial donors promised to offer 470 million
U.S. dollars of loans to Cambodia at the Tokyo conference.
</P>
<P>
France, which is one of Cambodia's biggest donor countries,
wishes to show a constant support to Cambodia's reconstruction in
the fields of economy, law, infrastructures and education, said
the foreign ministry.
</P>
<P>
French leaders will also discuss with Hun Sen the legal pursuit
against those held responsible for the genocide in the Khmer Rouge
era from 1975 to 1979. 
