<DOCNO> XIE19990601.0035 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Launches Sustainable Resource Management Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh Monday launched a
one-million-U.S.-dollar sustainable resource management project in
brackish water areas to establish an environmentally-sound,
economically viable and socially equitable community in the
country's coastal rice-shrimp culture zone.
</P>
<P>
This project, which is being aided by the United Nations
Development Program (UNDP), was launched under the sustainable
environment management program (SEMP), the national news agency
BSS reported.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to help make people aware of the
degradation of the environment and involve them in protecting the
quality of the eco-system, UNDP assistant resident representative
Shireen Kamal Sayeed was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
It would involve poor and marginal farmers in eco-friendly
demonstration activities and support the beneficiaries in
improving their sanitation practices and water supply, she said.
</P>
<P>
The Environment and Forest Ministry is executing a unique 26
million-dollar SEMP, and brackish water management project is one
of the major intervention areas of this largest ever UNDP-funded
environment program across the world, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
