<HEADLINE> France Calls on India and Pakistan to Resume Dialogue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, May 31 (Xinhua) -- France Monday called on India and
Pakistan to resume dialogue to prevent an escalation of the
tension which Paris said is harming the peace and stability in the
region.
</P>
<P>
The assistant spokesman of the French Foreign Ministry Francois
Rivasseau said that France is very concerned about the
continuation of confrontation at the Kashmir ``line of control''.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that a restoration of confidence between the
two countries would not be possible unless both sides do not
violate the control line and attack each other any more.
</P>
<P>
He welcomed the decision by Pakistan to send its foreign
minister to India soon.
</P>
<P>
Clashes have been taking between India and Pakistan in the
Kashmir region after Indian troops launched airstrikes against
Muslim guerrillas in Kashmir. 
