<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000 GMT, May 31 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA -- U.S. warplanes have begun to arrive at a military
base in western Turkey in a bid to expand air attacks against
Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, C-5 and C-17 cargo planes belonging to the U.S. Air
Forces carried logistic materials and NATO soldiers to the
Balikesir air base in western Turkey, the semi-official Anatolia
News Agency reported on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted a Turkish source, who asked not to be named,
as saying that F-16 and F-15 fighter jets of the U.S. Air Forces
have begun to arrive at the Balikesir base. (BC-Turkey-NATO)
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkey's Ankara State Security Court No. 2 on Monday
started trial of PKK leader Abdullah Ocalan on Imrali Island in
Marmara Sea near Turkey's western province of Bursa.
</P>
<P>
The court rejected a request of Ocalan's lawyers to postpone
the case before the trial started.
</P>
<P>
Intervenors and spectators were permitted to enter the court
hall, and only correspondents of Turkey's State Radio and
Television Corporation and Anatolian News Agency got the privilege
to take pictures in the hall. (BC-Turkey-PKK)
</P>
<P>
RIYADH -- The new Bahraini cabinet was sworn in before Emir
Sheikh Hamad Bin Isa al-Khalifa on Monday, according to media
reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Hamad expressed appreciation for the endeavor by Prime
Minister Sheikh Khalifa Bin Sulman al-Khalifa who was reappointed
by the emir to form the new cabinet. (BC-Bahrain-New Cabinet)
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraq and India on Monday signed an agreement on
economic and oil cooperation, the Iraqi News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
The accord was signed by Iraqi Oil Minister Amir Mohammed Rashid
and his Indian counterpart K. Ramamurthy who arrived here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Rashid said in a statement that the two countries agreed to
strengthen cooperation in the fields of industry, oil, agriculture
and trade. (BC-Iraq-India-Agreement)
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egypt will reopen the Pyramid of Cheops, the largest
of the famous Giza trio, on Thursday after more than a year of
repair work, an official in charge of antiquities said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Gaballah Ali Gaballah, secretary general of the Higher
Antiquities Council, told reporters that the Sphinx temple and
three tombs near the pyramid will also be opened to visitors at
the same time.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Culture Farouk Abdel Aziz Hosni will inaugurate the
opening ceremony. (BC-Egypt-Pyramid-Reopening) 
</P>
