<HEADLINE> Zanzibar in Power Blackout </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, May 31 (Xinhua) -- The Zanzibar Island, one of
the leading tourist attractions in east Africa, has been
experiencing power blackout for two days.
</P>
<P>
Engineers in Zanzibar said Monday that the outage is a result
of technical fault at the main transformer at Mtoni which receives
electricity from the mainland of Tanzania through a submarine
cable.
</P>
<P>
Reports said that a team of engineers from the state-owned
Tanzania Electric Supply Company Limited will arrive in Zanzibar
Tuesday to give a helping hand.
</P>
<P>
The blackout has exacerbated the water problem. Long lines of
people seeking water with containers and buckets are seen in
several areas, witnesses said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
