<HEADLINE> European Stock Markets Lack Clear Direction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Europe's stock markets except
Frankfurt registered final gains towards the end of a subdued
session Monday due to market holidays in both London and New York.
</P>
<P>
Paris' share prices closed a lackluster session higher,
supported by bargain hunting of selective stocks. The CAC-40 index
of leading French shares closed up 36.25 points at 4351.29.
</P>
<P>
The market was slightly weaker in early trading before climbing
back in the afternoon on bargain hunting of some of the index's
recent decliners.
</P>
<P>
In Zurich, strong buying of banking stocks helped the SMI jump
almost 124 points, or 1.82 percent, to end at 6911.6.
</P>
<P>
Modest Monday advances in Tokyo and Hongkong also helped
sentiment in Europe's markets, but German investors were more
cautious as the ECB warned of trouble ahead for Europe's largest
economy unless it underwent some major surgery.
</P>
<P>
The Xetra Dax of leading shares closed down 2.39 at 5068.59
from Friday's Xetra close. It traded between 5027.9 and 5116.4.
</P>
