<HEADLINE> Greek Police Arrest Eight Drug Smugglers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Greek police have in recent days
arrested eight Greek businessmen and Merchant Marine officers
suspected of smuggling a large quantity of cocaine to the U.S. and
Europe.
</P>
<P>
During the 10-month operation, coast guard and Finance
Ministry's Financial Crimes Squad, law enforcement officers raided
companies and residences in the cities such Athens and Piraeus,
and confiscated 440 million drachmas (about 1.5 million U.S.
dollars), police said Monday.
</P>
<P>
Police said they would continue to sort through the documents
seized during the raids and would be conducting checks on bank
accounts. 
