<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNICEF Day Marked at Horticulture Exposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The organizing committee of the
China '99 International Horticulture Exposition set aside today
for the United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF) activities as part
of International Children's Day.
</P>
<P>
Cui Zhitao, a member of the organizing committee, said on
behalf of the Chinese government at today's ceremony that China
has always paid a great deal of attention to protecting the rights
of children and that it is everyone's responsibility to leave a
greener and better home for children.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed his thanks for what UNICEF has done for
mankind and for Chinese children.
</P>
<P>
Representatives of UNICEF's Beijing office were present at
today's ceremony.
</P>
<P>
China restored its cooperative ties with UNICEF in 1979 and
since that time has received 230 million U.S. dollars worth of
donations from the organization.
</P>
<P>
The Exposition's theme is "Man and Nature: Towards the 21st
Century".  
</P>
</TEXT>
