<HEADLINE> Children in Southeastern Chinese City Saying "No" to War Toys </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, June 1 (Xinhua) -- About a thousand children in the
southeastern Chinese city of Wenzhou got rid of "war toys" today
to express their desire for peace.
</P>
<P>
This morning, children gathered at the Shangye Kindergarten to
throw their toy guns and knives into garbage cans while other
activities for International Children's Day were going on. "We are
children of the new age and don't want war or violence. We want a
future with green hope," they said all together.
</P>
<P>
Many parents who were present said that the world is far from
peaceful and that violence poses a great problem for children.
Something needs to be done early on to create a happy and peaceful
life, they said.
</P>
<P>
The organizers said that this action was not specifically
directed at toy manufacturers but was meant to deal with the
present special situation and to express children's hope for peace
and to create a better environment filled with love for them.
</P>
</TEXT>
