<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-01 14:49 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyprus-China Relations Excellent: President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus and China, though different
in size and geographically far apart, have had all along excellent
and friendly relations and sincere cooperation, Cyprus President
Glafcos Clerides said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In a written reply to Xinhua questions before his official
visit to China, which scheduled on June 6-11, Clerides said the
good ties are based on their common adherence to peace and
stability and the principles of the U.N. Charter.
</P>
<P>
He said the political dialogue between the two countries for
realization of common objectives was invigorated with the signing
in 1997 of a Protocol of Cooperation between the Ministries of
Foreign Affairs of our two countries.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, a number of bilateral agreements offer the legal
framework for further expansion of our relations in the fields of
trade, economy and technical cooperation, tourism, health, mass
media and information, culture and education, the President said.
</P>
<P>
Clerides said the Cypriot government attaches particular
importance to his forthcoming visit to China, hoping that "my
visit will be a milestone in our bilateral relations and will
give a new impetus to the close and fruitful cooperation in all
fields between our two countries".
</P>
<P>
China, with a remarkably enhanced international status, plays
today a constructive and active role in the world affairs. "We
attach, thus, great importance to our relationship with China
to the further growth of the ties between the two countries,"
the President stressed.
</P>
<P>
He said that in view of the longstanding friendship, the close
identity of our positions on major international and regional
issues and the determination of both sides to promote even further
the existing relations and the cooperation, there is ample ground
for further development of our relations.
</P>
<P>
Clerides also said that the Cyprus' people share the grief
of the Chinese people caused by the tragic death of three Chinese
journalists and many wounded as a result of the bombing of the
Embassy building in Belgrade, adding "we condemn outright the
bombing and express our sympathy to the People of China and to the
families of the victims."
</P>
<P>
"We also understand and respect the 'one China policy' of
the country," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Cypriot President expressed the appreciation to China's
"principled and constructive position" on the Cyprus issue.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
