<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Registration of New Voters Ends in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 1 (Xinhua) -- About 2,844 Macao residents were
registered as new voters in the past month, according to
statistics released Tuesday evening by the Administration and
Civil Service Department of the Macao government.
</P>
<P>
The registration for this year started on May 3 and ended at 7:
00 p.m. Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In this sense, there are 128,993 registered voters in Macao, an
increase of 2.2 percent over that of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
About 250,000 Macao residents are eligible for being registered
as voters. However, registered voters have been constituting about
half of the registrable population over the past several years.
</P>
<P>
Macao voters are not able to select the governor, who has been
sent to Macao by the Portuguese president. However, they can elect
some legislators.
</P>
<P>
At present, the 23-member Macao Legislative Assembly consists
of eight persons elected by voters, eight recommended by social
organizations, and seven appointed by the governor of Macao.
</P>
</TEXT>
