<HEADLINE> Rios Out of Semis of French Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Marcelo Rios failed to reach the last
four at the French Open on Tuesday, losing to Slovak Dominik
Hrbaty in four sets.
</P>
<P>
Hrbaty, ranked 30th in the world, won the tough competition 7-6,
6-2, 6-7, 6-2, booking his first ever semifinal at a Grand Slam
tournament.
</P>
<P>
Rios, seeded the ninth seed, was one of the gifted clay court
specialists and was widely tipped to win the tournament.
</P>
<P>
But the Chilean looked tired after his five-set defeat of
Spain's Alberto Berasategui in the previous round, unusually
making a series of unforced errors in the two hours and 28 minutes
match.
</P>
<P>
Hrbaty, the winner of the Prague tournament earlier this season,
ousted top seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov in the second round and had
also crushed Rios 6-2, 6-0 in their only previous encounter, in
Key Biscayne in March.
</P>
<P>
He is the second Slovak to make a Grand Slam semifinal this
year following Karol Kucera at the Australian Open. 
</P>
