<HEADLINE> HK Financial Secretary on Coming Middle East Trip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong Financial Secretary
Donald Tsang said Tuesday that his forthcoming trip to Middle East
countries is to strengthen ties with the region.
</P>
<P>
Tsang will lead a high-level mission to Dubai in the United
Arab Emirates, and the Gulf state of Bahrain from June 5 to 8.
</P>
<P>
The major objective of the mission is to explore ways to expand
Hong Kong's business partnership with the Middle East and maximize
its huge potential, especially as a services market.
</P>
<P>
Tsang said: "The mission of the trip is to strengthen our ties
with and project a higher commercial profile Hong Kong has in this
gateway to the Middle East."
</P>
<P>
Dubai and Hong Kong bear many similarities. "We both are the
leading trading center, transportation and tourism hub of the
region. Similarly, Bahrain is the financial center of the Middle
East. There are ample business opportunities between Hong Kong and
the region," he said.
</P>
<P>
"It is important to get the message to our trading partners
that Hong Kong has come a long way with our economic adjustment.
There are signs that our economy has bottomed out and that costs
are coming down in significant terms. The East Asian region as a
whole offers a good buy and stands ready for foreign investment,"
he added.
</P>
<P>
Organized by the Trade Development Council, the mission is also
a strategic initiative to stimulate exports of consumer products
and further diversify Hong Kong's portfolio of a promising
emerging market.
</P>
<P>
Accompanying Tsang on the visit will be Michael Sze, executive
director of the Trade Development Council, and 10 senior
executives from major Hong Kong banks, manufacturers, traders and
service providers. 
</P>
