<HEADLINE> Seles In Semis, Rios Out of French Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Third-seeded Monica Seles of the
United States scored a straight sets victory over Conchita
Martinez of Spain on Tuesday to seal a place in the semi-finals of
the French Open women's singles.
</P>
<P>
Seles, a three-time winner of the title, beat unseeded Martinez
6-1, 6-4 and will play five-time champion Steffi Graf of Germany
as the latter defeated Lindsay Davenport in three sets earlier.
</P>
<P>
The other women's semifinalists were top-ranked Martina Hingis
and defending champion Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario.
</P>
<P>
On the men's side, a sluggish Marcelo Rios made a surprise
early exit from a tournament he seemed primed to win.
</P>
<P>
He fell 7-6 (7-4), 6-2, 6-7 (6-8), 6-3 to Dominik Hrbaty of
Slovakia, one of this year's big surprises who knocked out top-
ranked Yevgeny Kafelnikov in straight sets in the second round.
</P>
<P>
Graf, a five-time champion in Paris, missed last year's French
Open because of injuries, produced one of her best victories of
late.
</P>
<P>
In their first meeting on clay, Graf was overpowering in the
first set, and after Davenport came back in the second by winning
a tiebreaker, she broke Davenport twice in the third set to win 6-
1,6-7 (5-7), 6-3.
</P>
<P>
Graf will play Seles, a finalist last year, who had an easy
time with Conchita Martinez of Spain.
</P>
<P>
Hingis surged into the semis with a commanding 6-2, 6-2 victory
over Austrian Schwartz who ranked 125th, while Sanchez-Vicario had
an easy time, defeating another Austrian Sylvia Plischke, 6-2, 6-4.
</P>
