<HEADLINE> Coastal Parts of China Preparing for Typhoon Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 1 (Xinhua) -- China's coastal cities are
preparing for the typhoon season this year, it was announced at a
typhoon conference that opened here today.
</P>
<P>
The incidence of Western Pacific tropical storms and typhoons
this year is higher than it was last year and China is expecting
more typhoons, meteorologists say.
</P>
<P>
Typhoons are the major disaster in China's coastal areas, which
have a combined gross domestic product of about 3 trillion yuan (
about 390 billion US dollars) a year and play an important role in
the national economy, said an expert with the State flood Control
and Drought Relief Headquarters. Disaster relief work in these
areas is vital to the nation's economy.
</P>
<P>
Coastal areas have already begun improving sea dykes and dams
and the overall disaster control capacity. Improvements on alarms
and telecommunications networks will also be speeded up. 
</P>
</TEXT>
