<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) on Tuesday
called on Israel to make a fresh drive in an effort to push the
Middle East peace process forward.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters after a meeting with Egyptian Foreign
Minister Amr Moussa, EU Mideast envoy Miguel Moratinos expressed
EU's hope that the future would witness no crisis pertaining to
the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Hopes of reviving the Arab-Israeli peace talks increased after
Israel's moderate Ehud Barak defeated hardline Prime Minister
Benjamin Netanyahu in the country's May 17 general elections.
</P>
<P>
Little progress has been made in the peace negotiations since
Netanyahu came to power in 1996 due to his intransigent policies.
</P>
<P>
Moratinos reiterated the importance of the role played by both
Egypt and the EU in the peace march, saying that the EU plans to
shoulder its responsibilities.
</P>
<P>
The 15-nation European organization is ready to help smooth
away any obstacles that impede the realization of peace in the
Middle East, he said.
</P>
<P>
The EU, which desires to play a key role in the Mideast peace
process, keeps close contacts with Egypt, the first Arab country
to sign a peace treaty with Israel and an active mediator in the
Arab-Israeli peacemaking. 
