missed last year's French Open due to injuries, defeated Lindsay
Davenport to advance to the semifinals of the French Open on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In their first meeting on clay, Graf overpowered Davenport in
the first set but the American came back in the second, winning in
a tiebreaker before Graf broke Davenport twice in the third set to
win 6-1, 6-7 (5-7), 6-3.
</P>
<P>
In the semifinals, she will likely face Monica Seles as both
Martina Hingis and Arantxa Sanchez-Vicario also won their
respective matches earlier.
</P>
<P>
It took Hingis an hour to dismantle 125th-ranked Barbara
Schwartz 6-2, 6-2, while Sanchez-Vicario had an easy time to
defeat another Austrian Sylvia Plischke 6-2, 6-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
