to use surplus cash to buy back government bonds outstanding,
partly because of worries that the move might complicate already-
tense administration relations with Congress over next year's
budget.
</P>
<P>
-- Russian President Boris Yeltsin filled the remaining posts
in a new government Monday, ending a struggle for ministerial
portfolios that analysts say endangers the country's economy and
fragile democratic institutions. 
