<HEADLINE> Chinese, Sierra Leonean Presidents Hold Talks (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin, in a
meeting with Sierra Leone's President Ahmad Tejan Kabbah in
Beijing's Great Hall of the People this afternoon, discussed
bilateral ties and issues of common concern.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that since China and Sierra Leone established
diplomatic ties 28 years ago they have had fruitful cooperation in
political, economic, military and other areas, and have supported
and cooperated with each other in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government appreciates Sierra Leone's efforts in
promoting bilateral relations and its support for the "One China"
policy and not having official contacts with Taiwan, Jiang said,
expressing his thanks for Sierra Leone's support for China's
reunification cause.
</P>
<P>
Sierra Leone is rich in resources and there is a great deal of
potential in bilateral economic and trade cooperation, he said,
adding that the Chinese government places great importance on its
relations with Sierra Leone and encourages enterprises in mutually-
beneficial cooperation with Sierra Leone in various ways and in
exploring new spheres to further promote bilateral ties.
</P>
