<HEADLINE> Chinese, Sierra Leonean Presidents Hold Talks (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jiang said that the Chinese government has been concerned about
the situation in Sierra Leone and sympathizes with its people in
their suffering from the war and appreciates the efforts of the
people led by President Kabbah in seeking national peace and
stability.
</P>
<P>
China supports the Economic Community of West African States in
trying to restore peace to the country and will continue to push
for international support for the peace process and reconstruction
of Sierra Leone, Jiang said, and expressed hope that the west
African country will have a comprehensive peace soon with normal
order restored.
</P>
<P>
Kabbah said that relations with China were established on a
basis of mutual respect and concern and have grown smoothly over
the years and that the people and government of Sierra Leone are
grateful to China for its strong support for the country's efforts
to achieve political stability and economic development.
</P>
<P>
In the course of reconstruction, he said, Sierra Leone realizes
the vital importance of national security and stability to
economic progress.
</P>
<P>
After Beijing, Kabbah and his party will visit Shanghai, Wuhan,
and Shenzhen, where, he said, they want to learn more about
China's experience with the reforms, opening up and development.
</P>
<P>
After the talks, the two presidents attended a signing ceremony
for economic and technological cooperation agreements between the
two governments.
</P>
<P>
Jiang also held a banquet in Kabbah's honor.  
