<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Morocco and Egypt will convene the
third session of a joint higher committee next week in Rabat,
Moroccan ambassador in Cairo said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Moroccan King Hassan II and Egyptian President Hosni Mubarak
will co-chair the session of the Higher Moroccan-Egyptian
Committee, which started its work in 1996, next Tuesday,
Ambassador Abdellatif Mouline told Egypt's Middle East News Agency.
</P>
<P>
