Moroccan diplomat said that it forms part of the continued
consultations between the two sides on the Arab situation and the
accomplishments which have been made since the second session of
the joint committee.
</P>
<P>
He termed the signing of a free trade zone agreement on April
19 as the foremost accomplishment.
</P>
<P>
The coming meetings of the committee will cover proposals on
increasing bilateral trade volume, operating regular maritime
lines between the two countries, forming joint trade firms for
marketing the two countries' commodities and a private sector bank
to guarantee exports.
</P>
<P>
The annual trade volume between Egypt and Morocco stood at 33
million U.S. dollars in 1998. 
