the signing of Sirte Accord in mid-April by DRC President Laurent
Kabila and Museveni.
</P>
<P>
Chad has reportedly completed withdrawal of its troops deployed
in northern DRC. Uganda has decided to pull out of southwestern
DRC and Rwanda declared in late May that it is willing to exercise
a unilateral cease-fire in the DRC.
</P>
<P>
Analysts hold that this is a great stride forward to the final
peaceful settlement of the DRC conflict. 
