<HEADLINE> mee060110hke - Israel Uses Low-Sulphur Diesel Oil to Cut Pollution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Israel's transport market
officially switched to the use of the 0.05 percent low-sulphur
diesel fuel Tuesday in an effort to reduce air pollution,
</P>
<P>
Environmental officials said the switch is to reduce levels of
air pollution by motor vehicles, especially in populated areas,
according to the Globes business newspaper.
</P>
<P>
By using low-sulphur diesel oil, air pollution can be reduced
by 30 percent, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
The Egged Company, the biggest bus company in Israel, said it
has already finished the transition to the use of low-sulphur
diesel fuel.
</P>
<P>
Environmental officials said Israel must work to make further
improvement in fuel products within a few years in order to catch
up with Europe, which is making preparation for the switch to the
use of 0.02 percent low-sulphur diesel oil. 
</P>
