<HEADLINE> HK's External Trade Down in March 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The volume of Hong Kong's total
exports decreased by 6.2 percent over a year earlier in March 1999,
according to statistics released by the Census and Statistics
Department here today.
</P>
<P>
Concurrently, the volume of imports dropped by 8.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
Comparing the first three months of 1999 with the same period a
year earlier, the volume of Hong Kong's re-exports decreased by 4.
1 percent, and the volume of domestic exports by 9.1 percent.
Taken together, the volume of total exports decreased by 4.7
percent. Meanwhile, imports fell by 10.2 percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Comparing March 1999 with March 1998, the prices of re-exports
and domestic exports fell by 4.2 percent and 3.0 percent
respectively. Import prices also declined by 3.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
As regards to price changes in the first three months of 1999
over the same period a year earlier, the prices of re-exports and
domestic exports were down by 4.6 percent and 2.6 percent
respectively, and import prices by 3.6 percent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
