<HEADLINE> Macao, Guangdong Officials Hold Meeting on Border Affairs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The Macao-Guangdong Border Affairs
Coordination Group held its annual meeting here on today to
strengthen the cooperation between the two places in combating
cross-border crimes and smuggling.
</P>
<P>
Domingos Fezas Vital, an advisor to the Macao governor and head
of the Macao delegation to the meeting, said that information
exchanges have been much improved in recent years and the two
sides have made marked achievements in jointly fighting crimes.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Macao is a small place with a population of over
400,000. Due to convenient border crossing, however, some 30
million persons traversed the border connecting Macao with
Guangdong Province in 1998.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore, we need the help and cooperation from our
neighboring area," Vital said. "The meeting enhanced mutual trust
and we have full confidence in the cooperative measures in the
future."
</P>
<P>
Chao Zhenwei, deputy secretary-general of the Guangdong
provincial government and head of the Guangdong delegation, said
after the meeting that the two sides reviewed the work in the past
year and discussed issues of common concern "with a sincere
attitude."
</P>
<P>
Chao said that the coordination and contact between Guangdong
and Macao will be carried on even after China resumes the
sovereignty over Macao on December 20 this year.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, the two sides also agreed to clean up the
waters surrounding Macao to ensure better shipping.
</P>
<P>
The coordination group was set up in 1987, and annual meetings
have been held in Macao and Guangdong by turns.  
</P>
</TEXT>
