<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Jobless Rate Sets New Record of 6 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Macao's unemployment rate between
February and April of this year stood at six percent, the highest
in the 1990s, and 0.3 percentage point higher than that in the
January-March period this year, the latest official statistics
show.
</P>
<P>
As compared with the same period in 1998, the February-April
period jobless rate was 2.4 percentage points higher, according to
figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the underemployment rate in the period remained
unchanged at 1.2 percent in comparison with the first three months
of this year, and down 0.3 percentage point from the February-
April period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Local economists pointed out that the government does not have
a good plan in the near future to pull down the high jobless rate,
and Macao has been affected by overall economic depression over
the past few years. To be worse, new graduates in the summer may
push the rate even higher.
</P>
<P>
One of the stopgap measures should be fewer workers introduced
from outside Macao, a local labor union leader noted.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
