At the Potala Palace in Lhasa, the Tibet region's capital, over
2,000 local children wore festive costumes at a national flag-
raising ceremony to show their loyalty to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
One 9-year old boy in Jinan, the capital of Shandong Province,
gave a 37-meter-long painting that he had worked on for half a
year, showing the changes and development in his hometown, and
said that it will be sent to Macao as a gift for children there
for the return of Macao to China on December 20. 
</P>
