<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The Second Artillery Force under
the People's Liberation Army (PLA) and Northwest China Engineering
University in Xi'an recently announced plans to join in a
cooperative effort to train more high quality personnel for the
missile force.
</P>
<P>
Today's Guangming Daily reported that the university will
become a base for fostering personnel for the missile force.
</P>
<P>
The Daily noted that the project is part of the PLA's effort to
implement President Jiang Zemin's call for using science and
technology to build a powerful PLA.
</P>
<P>
