channels to nurture high quality military personnel and promote
the further development of military colleges, it said.
</P>
<P>
The Second Artillery Force has enlisted a substantial number of
university graduates and postgraduates in recent years, including
many enlistees who have since been promoted to the senior command
level or are otherwise missile experts.
</P>
<P>
The agreement between the two parties calls for the university
to supply the force with a required number of outstanding
graduates and postgraduates each year, with the force responsible
for selecting officers to attend postgraduate courses.
</P>
<P>
The missile force will also establish a defense fund to provide
support for outstanding students who agree to join the army after
graduation.  
