<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Bans Import of Jordanian Cloven-Footed Animals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- China has stopped importing cloven-
footed animals from Jordan, where the animals have been hit by
outbreaks of foot-and-mouth disease and some other similar
diseases.
</P>
<P>
China suspended the import of pigs, cattle and goats as well as
their products from Jordan as of May 12, according to a notice
released recently by the State Administration for Entry-Exit
Inspection and Quarantine.
</P>
<P>
The notice said all cloven-footed livestock and side-line
products brought in by travelers or via mail from that country
will be confiscated and destroyed.
</P>
<P>
Cloven-footed animals and their products carried by ships,
aircraft or trains that come from Jordan and travel through or
stay for a period in China will be quarantined for safekeeping.
</P>
<P>
Seized animals and products smuggled in from Jordan will be
destroyed under the supervision of nearby quarantine departments,
the notice said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
