<HEADLINE> Quake Jolts Southern Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A quake measuring 4.4 degrees on the
Richter scale Monday night jolted the south of Shiraz in Iran's
southern Far province, the Islamic Repubic News Agency reported on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The tremor occurred at 23:41 local time (1911 GMT) and its
epicenter was 50 kilometers south of Shiraz, the provincial
capital, the seismological base of the Geophysics Institution
affiliated to Tehran University announced.
</P>
<P>
No report is immediatley available about any possible
casualties or damages.
</P>
<P>
Another 4.8-degree quake hit region on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Two powerful earthquakes measuring 6.8 and 5.9 degrees rocked
the region on May 7, killing 28 people and injuring more than 100
others.
</P>
<P>
Since then, hundreds of after-shocks and over 10 earthquakes
measuring over four degrees have been registered.
</P>
<P>
Experts believed that more after-shocks would continue in the
region till the end of the hot season and that strong and mild
after-shocks would continue to hit the area until September.
</P>
</TEXT>
