<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Zambia has received investment
pledges amounting to 36.6 million U.S. dollars from January to
April this year, the Investment Center (IC) has said.
</P>
<P>
According to the Zambia Investment News available here Tuesday
from the Investment Center, the manufacturing sector accounts for
over 20 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural sector has the second highest pledged
investment amounting to 5.4 million dollars in which about 270
jobs are expected to be created.
</P>
<P>
Tourism is the third highest recipient of investment pledges in
this period with accumulated pledges amounting to 4.7 million
dollars.
</P>
<P>
In order to attract more investment, Zambia's tourist capital,
Livingstone, has decided to host a three-day festival of Zambian
arts and music which is set to become an internationally
recognized annual event.
</P>
<P>
The festival, which is being coordinated by a company called
"Africa Vision", is set for September 17-19 this year.
</P>
<P>
Zambia Daily Mail newspaper Tuesday quoted festival coordinator
Ali Shenton as saying that the occasion would help market
Livingstone as a tourism destination and bring more investment to
the country.
</P>
<P>
The festival would feature live Zambian bands, traditional
dances and music workshops. Street theatre, acrobats, comedy and
puppet shows would be other attractions.
</P>
<P>
Artists would also be given a chance to exhibit their works
during the festival while photographic competitions would also be
there, he said. 
</P>
