<DOCNO> XIE19990601.0196 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks rose 216.44
points, or 1.78 percent, to close at 12,363.56 Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Finance, Utilities, Properties and Commerce and Industry made
across-the-board increases of 2.48 percent, 0.71 percent, 1.78
percent and 1.81 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index went up 3.97 percent and
the Hang Seng China-affiliated Corporations Index up 1.79 percent.
</P>
<P>
Tuesday's market turnover was 4.403 billion HK dollars (564
million U.S. dollars), 381 million HK dollars (or 48 million U.S.
dollars) more than Monday's market turnover of 4.022 billion HK
dollars (516 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index lost 7.15 points, or 0.06 percent, to
open at 12,139.97 Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The HSI gained 3.91 points, or 0.03 percent, to finish the
morning session at 12,151.03. 
</P>
</TEXT>
