<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yugoslavia's Voice Should Be Heard: FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Any plans to resolve the Kosovo
issue should take the views of Yugoslavia into consideration,
China's Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao has stressed here
today.
</P>
<P>
"We have noticed Yugoslavia's response that it will accept the
agreement of the G-8 foreign ministers' meeting on the
precondition that its sovereignty and territorial integrity are
safeguarded," said Zhu.
</P>
<P>
China has consistently advocated a peaceful and just solution
to the crisis through dialogue, Zhu reiterated, adding that the
airstrikes against Yugoslavia is a matter of priority. "otherwise,
a formal solution has nowhere to start," he noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
