<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-01 07:24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading Turkish Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items
in leading Turkish newspapers on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Sabah (Morning):
</P>
<P>
-- Turkey's Ankara State Security Court No. 2 Monday started
trial of Abdullah Ocalan, leader of the Kurdish Workers' Party
(PKK), on Imrali Island in Marmara Sea near Turkey's western
province of Bursa.
</P>
<P>
Ocalan pleaded for sparing his life in the court, saying that "
I would like to state my determination to work for peace and
brotherhood within the democratic republic" if he could avoid the
death penalty.
</P>
<P>
Hurriyet (Freedom):
</P>
<P>
-- U.S. warplanes have begun to arrive at a military base in
western Turkey in a bid to expand air attacks against Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, C-5 and C-17 cargo planes belonging to the U.S. Air
Force carried logistic materials and NATO soldiers to the
Balikesir air base in western Turkey.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that 36 U.S. fighter jets will be deployed at
the air base in Balikesir and other 18 U.S. warplanes will be
deployed at the air base in Bandirma.
</P>
<P>
Milliyet (National):
</P>
<P>
-- Turkish Foreign Ministry warned Greece about its attempts
to claim sovereignty over islets at the Aegean Sea with
undetermined status through unofficial organizations.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Bulent Ecevit also warned Greece about its
preference for creating fait accomplis instead of dialogue and
escalating tensions between the two neighboring countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
