<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sydney Olympics Organisers to Reconsider Cycling Site </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The Sydney Organising Committee
for the Olympic Games (SOCOG) is to reconsider the site for
Olympic road cycling racesSYDNEY, June 1 (AFP) - Sydney Olympic
organisers under pressure from the international cycling
federation.
</P>
<P>
The SOCOG's Sports Commission will consider six potential
courses before passing on its preferred option to the
International Olympic Committee and the international Cycling
Union (UCI) for approval, according to SOCOG's general manager for
sport Bob Elphinston on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The UCI asked SOCOG to reconsider switching the road races from
Moore Park to Bankstown following a reported request from Rupert
Murdoch's Fox Studios.
</P>
<P>
Fox said it would lose as much as 3.9 million U.S. dollars from
a five-day closure of its studios and entertainment complex in
Moore Park.
</P>
<P>
It would have also cost SOCOG about 1.3 million U.S. dollars to
remove speed humps and roundabouts from the route. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
