</P>
<P>
-- Federal Alliance (MF)
</P>
<P>
-- Inkatha Freedom Party (IFP)
</P>
<P>
-- Minority Front (MF)
</P>
<P>
-- New National Party (NNP)
</P>
<P>
-- pan Africanist Congress of Azania (PAC)
</P>
<P>
-- The Government By The People green Party (GPGP)
</P>
<P>
-- Socialist Party of Azania (SOPA)
</P>
<P>
-- United Christian Democratic Party (UCDF)
</P>
<P>
-- United Democratic Movement (UDM)
</P>
<P>
-- Vryheidsfront (Freedom Front, FF)
</P>
<P>
-- Abolition of Income Tax and Usury Party (AITUP).
</P>
<P>
All the above-mentioned parties will contest for the 400
parliamentary seats, and another 10 parties will take part in the
provincial-level polls only:
</P>
<P>
-- People's Liberation Party (for Western Cape)
</P>
<P>
-- National Coalition Party (for Western Cape)
</P>
<P>
-- Workers International Vanguard League (for Western Cape )
</P>
<P>
-- Africa Moral Party ( for Western Cape )
</P>
<P>
-- DabaLorivhuwa Patriotic Front (for Northern Cape )
</P>
<P>
-- Ximoko ( for Northern Cape )
</P>
<P>
-- Labor Party (for Gauteng )
</P>
<P>
-- Sindawonye Progressive Party (for Mpumalanga )
</P>
<P>
-- Unemployment Labor Alliance (for Free State )
</P>
<P>
-- Mass United Movement (for Kwazulu-Natal )
</P>
<P>
</P>
