<HEADLINE> AVC Cup Men's Tournament to Open on Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, Anhui province, June 1 (Xinhua) -- The first Asian
Volleyball Confederation (AVC) Cup men's club tournament will make
its debut here on Wednesday, providing an arena for the elite
clubs of Asian countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The six-day event features the league winners of five countries
including NEC Blue Rockets of Japan, Samsung Fire and Marine
Insurance club of South Korea, Ai Rayan club of Qatar, Paykan club
of Iran and Sichuan Fulan club of China.
</P>
<P>
The original version of the event is the Asian Club
Championship which came to an end for the great gap between the
participating teams resulting from the orignial open registration
system on the clubs' own will.
</P>
<P>
"The Asian club championship cannot go on for it failed to draw
enough attention from both the spectators and sponsors, so it has
came to a blind alley," said Liu Wenbing, the assistant treasurer
of AVC.
</P>
<P>
Liu said that in view of the lackluster performances of the
championship, AVC decided to launch the AVC Cup men's club
tournament where the teams should qualify as the winner of this
season in their country leagues.
</P>
<P>
"This aims to raise the level of the competition and enhance
the appeal of the regional event," Liu said.
</P>
<P>
The hosts China is allowed to field two elite clubs including
Sichuan Fu Lan and Chengdu Army club which came in first and third
respectively in China's national volleyball league this season.
</P>
<P>
The event also moves into line with the international practices
including the rally point scoring system and colorful balls.
</P>
</TEXT>
