<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Host International Pediatrics Congress </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 1 (Xinhua) -- China will host the 23rd
International Pediatrics and the Second International Congress on
Pediatric Nursing between September 9-14, 2001, in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The two events will be the first of their kind held in China.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese Medical Association (CMA), the host agency, said
that the theme of the congress will focus on "Children's
Healthcare in the New Millennium". The topic will cover 30 fields
related to pediatrics and children.
</P>
<P>
The International Pediatric Association (IPA), one of the
world's largest medical organizations, has 136 member countries
and regions. The congress, which is held every three years and
usually attracts 4,000-5,000 participants, deals with all areas
concerning children and pediatrics. The congress is regarded as
the most important of international events concerning children.
</P>
<P>
The CMA praised China for its effort to extend medical care and
protection to the country's over 360 million children. The agency
also expressed hope that the congress will provide China with
useful information concerning healthcare for children in other
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
