<HEADLINE> UAE, Britain to Hold Talks on Kosovo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Defense officials of the United
Arab Emirates (UAE) and Britain are to hold talks in London on
Tuesday, centering on Kosovo and military cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Mohammed Bin Zayed Al-Nahyan, the Chief of Staff of the
UAE Armed Forces, who is heading a delegation, will hold talks
with British Defense Secretary George Robertson, the Gulf News
daily reported.
</P>
<P>
The talks are to be held under the auspices of the Britain-UAE
Joint Defense Committee, which was established after the signing
of the Defense Cooperation Accord between the two countries in
1996.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the continuing air strikes on Yugoslavia
launched by the North Atlantic Treaty Organization, the
discussions will also involve future joint activities between
British and UAE Armed Forces, including training and exercises.
</P>
<P>
The current meeting will be the second of the Joint Defense
Committee. The first took place in Abu Dhabi after the accord took
effect in March 1998. 
</P>
