<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka to Set Up Environmental Authorities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka will set up environmental
authorities in provinces in an effort to solve environmental
problems expeditiously and effectively, the official Daily News
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Environment Nandimithra Ekanayake was quoted as
saying that there were now delays in finding solutions to
environmental problems but with decentralization such delays would
be eliminated.
</P>
<P>
He urged teachers to play a key role in educating the children
about the environment and proposed sending teachers abroad for
training in environmental studies.
</P>
<P>
At present there are 1,400 environmental brigades in the
country and the target of his ministry is to increase the number
to 2,000 by the end of this year, he said.
</P>
<P>
These brigades aim to promote knowledge on the environment
among students to help take the environmental message to the
people.
</P>
<P>
The ministry also aims to create awareness on conservation and
practical environmental activities, the minister said. 
