<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Lijiang's Sister River Charming Tourists with Virgin Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUILIN, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Deriving from the same source
mountain of "Mao'er" as Lijiang River that runs through southwest
China's scenic city of Guilin, Zijiang River is charming tourists
with its completely intact ecological environment.
</P>
<P>
The poetic beauty of its sister Lijiang has been well known
around the world, which attracts annually 8.5 million tourists to
Guilin. Zijiang, however, has been up to now relatively unknown.
</P>
<P>
The river gushes down from 2,140 meters above sea level and
runs 22.5 km through bamboo forests and steep cliffs. It boasts
the most uncontaminated water in Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
To better protect the "Golden River", the local government has
urged that residential and industrial sewage and waste discharge
into the river should cease.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 560 million yuan of World Bank loans has been
provided to protect the upper stretches of the Lijiang from soil
erosion. And the city government has raised another 200 million
yuan to carry out a facelift of tourist spots along the river's
banks.
</P>
<P>
The two Guilin rivers are valuable tourist destinations, where
the landscape and ethnic customs have attracted at least seven
million visitors from 130 countries and regions and 100 million
Chinese tourists over the past 20 years.
</P>
<P>
In an environmental assessment of 46 key Chinese cities
conducted by the National Administration of Environmental
Protection last year, the city of Guilin was top of the list.
</P>
<P>
The city has 29 hotels in various categories and the new
Liangjiang International Airport has become the largest airport in
China's midwest region, handling ten million passengers annually.
It is now capable of receiving one million overseas tourists and
10 million domestic travelers every year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990601.0272 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-06-01 </DATE_TIME>
