<HEADLINE> Handicapped Doctor Enjoys International Acclaim </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, June 1 (Xinhua) -- A man crippled with rheumatoid
arthritis for two decade has now miraculously cured his own
disease and become an international star as a result of the
treatment he used.
</P>
<P>
Qu Jianye became paralyzed as a result of contracting
rheumatoid arthritis 24 years ago, when he was 18 years old. Over
the next 11 years, he devoted himself to traditional medical study
followed by another four years' clinical practice.
</P>
<P>
After he became a doctor, Qu has used his skill to help many
paralyzed rheumatoid arthritis patients recover.
</P>
<P>
Qu's new theory in treating the disease also attracted
worldwide interest, and his essay on this topic even was awarded a
golden medal at an international conference on Chinese traditional
medicine. 
</P>
