<HEADLINE> Gullit Set to Put Future in Newcastle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Newcastle United boss Ruud Gullit is
set to end speculation over his future at the club by signing a
new extended contract on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Dutchman arrived on Tyneside last August and despite
leading the Magpies to the FA Cup Final, is yet to put pen to
paper on the two-year deal which was tabled at the time.
</P>
<P>
But after receiving assurances on cash for rebuilding his squad,
the 36-year-old is preparing to commit his immediate future to the
Magpies beyond next season.
</P>
<P>
Lawyers for the club and the manager have been in discussion
for some time over the details of the deal but Gullit's agent, Jon
Smith, has admitted that the talking is all but done and he is
expected to put pen to paper within weeks.
</P>
<P>
"We are talking to Newcastle about extending Ruud's contract
beyond next season," Smith said.
</P>
<P>
"He's a very wealthy man and money has never really been an
issue.
</P>
<P>
"When he came to Newcastle, they made an offer and we accepted
it. The only issue cash-wise is how much Ruud has to spend on the
team, and in fairness, the Board has been very forthcoming on that.
"
</P>
<P>
The news will come as a relief to Newcastle fans, who have
shown their approval of Gullit's methods in recent months despite
some indifferent form and poor results. 
</P>
</TEXT>
