<HEADLINE> Laudrup Quits FC Copenhagen </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Danish international Brian
Laudrup made a stunning statement, saying he was to leave FC
Copenhagen.
</P>
<P>
The famous midfielder said in a TV interview: "I didn't enjoy
playing anymore. And the joy didn't come back with (former club)
Chelsea, nor with FC Copenhagen."
</P>
<P>
"It has not been hard to see that I have not been able to give
more than 70 percent of myself. I just had no more to give,"
Laudrup said.
</P>
<P>
Laudrup gave no indication of his plans for the future. But
English premier league club Chelsea has first choice should
Laudrup opt to play elsewhere, but it was not immediately clear
whether the 30-year old Dane would quit the game for good.
