<HEADLINE> Udinese Beat Juventus to Gain UEFA Spot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 31 (Xinhua) -- Udinese upset former European
champions Juventus to take a UEFA Cup spot on Monday when they
forced Juventus to a 1-1 tie in the second leg of a play-off match.
</P>
<P>
The two teams played to a goalless draw in the first leg and
Juventus lost the two-leg series on the away goal rule.
</P>
<P>
Juventus, champions of Europe in 1996 and beaten finalists in
the following two years, now have to try for a UEFA Cup berth via
the Intertoto Cup.
</P>
<P>
Juventus looked to have done enough to book a place in the UEFA
Cup when Filippo Inzaghi converted a penalty shot at the 23rd
minute.
</P>
<P>
But Udinese rallied in the second half and got the equaliser
after 71 minutes through Paolo Poggi, who slammed home a close
range shot. 
</P>
</TEXT>
