<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kirghizstan Establishes Frontier Force </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, June 1 (Xinhua) -- Kirghizstanian President Askar
Akayevich Akayev issued a decree Monday to set up Kirghizstan's
own national frontier force.
</P>
<P>
Under the decree, the Kirghizstanian national frontier force
will be composed of members from the Frontier Bureau of the
Defense Ministry and from the National Security Bureau, an
official from the President's Office told a news conference in
Bishkek on the day.
</P>
<P>
He said his country will gradually set up a unified national
frontier force.
</P>
<P>
Borders of Kirghizstan have been guarded by Russian frontier
forces since the collapse of the Soviet Union in 1991.
</P>
<P>
The official added that the establishment of such a frontier
force doesn't mean that Russian troops should pull out of
Kirghizstan immediately.
</P>
<P>
Kirghizstan and Russia are consulting each other to map out a
cooperation agreement between the two frontier forces and a hand-
over plan.
</P>
<P>
The Russian side has set up a special team to help Kirghizstan
form its own frontier force, the official said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
