<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Antarctic Treaty Meeting Opens in Peru </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, 31 May (Xinhua)-- The 23rd consultative meeting of the
Antarctic Treaty was opened officially here on Monday by Peru's
Foreign Minister Fernando de Trazegnies.
</P>
<P>
President of the meeting and head of the Peruvian delegation,
Carlos Alzamora Traverso, said the cooperation of developed
countries with developing nations can be a key factor in the
protection of the Antarctic environment.
</P>
<P>
Revealing that the question of cooperation in Antarctic
environmental protection was included in this meeting's agenda
thanks to a petition from his country, Traverso said that
cooperation is already in process, "but it has to do with
bilateral agreements."
</P>
<P>
De Trazegnies expressed his desire of maintaining the Antarctic
as a zone of peace, understanding, concord and mutual help in a
world torn by conflicts and tensions.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, attended by 42 delegations of the member countries
and regions of the Antarctic Treaty and of international
organizations, will end on Friday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
